Probably from {{etyl|non}} ''[[veifa]]'' ‘move around, wave’, related to Latin ''[[vibrare]]''.

====Verb====
{{en-verb|weav|es}}

# To make or move by [[turn]]ing and [[twist]]ing.
#: ''The ambulance had to '''weave''' its way through traffic to reach the accident.''
# To make (a path or way) by [[wind]]ing in and out or from side to side.
#: ''The ambulance '''weaved''' its way through the heavy traffic.''

